publisher.pictorical.com
------------------------

to switch from master to a new branch
$ git checkout -b [branch] master

to switch from master to an existing branch
$ git checkout [branch]

to push to that branch
$ git push origin [branch]

to switch from a branch to master
$ git checkout master

to merge a branch to github
$ git checkout master (if not already)
$ git merge --no-ff [branch]
$ git branch -d [branch]
$ git push origin master
$ git push origin :[branch] // this will delete the branch in the repo

to pull changes
$ git pull origin [branch or master]

*note: you always want to pull changes after an others push

in the very rare case there are conflicts
$ git mergetool

